This was, without a doubt, the worst Japanese food I've ever had the unfortunate experience of trying. I just disposed of a salmon teriyaki bento box, so I got a chance to try multiple dishes of mediocrity. The California roll tasted as though it had been made several hours, if not days earlier. The dumplings were over-done and tasteless. The spring rolls were tough, and nearly void of all filling and flavor. The fried rice, again, tasted as though it was days old. It was mushy, barely holding its shape, and turned into a gritty paste upon consumption. The noodles too, were clearly old, as they had the distinctly cold center of microwaved food. The salmon was tasteless, and so overcooked it was brittle, falling apart easily (and not in the good way). Finally, they inexplicably included some form of uninspired spicy mayo instead of a sauce for the dumplings or spring rolls, and a bland, sad excuse for teriyaki that clearly lent its lack of flavor to the salmon. This was atrocious. I could not be more disappointed in a meal if it did not exist at all.
